annotationA: Meiotic recombination protein W68; Required for meiotic recombination. Together with mei-P22, mediates DNA cleavage that forms the double-strand breaks (DSB) that initiate meiotic recombination (By similarity)
annotationB: Structural maintenance of chromosomes 5, isoform E; SUMO ligase activity; damaged DNA binding; ATPase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: mitotic nuclear division; cellular response to DNA damage stimulus; mitotic sister chromatid segregation; DNA repair; response to caffeine; double-strand break repair via homologous recombination
